commit.message: This is real seed data hopefully
Updated IS keys and fixed lat,long coors
Fixed bug with config production setting in dev
Fixed location not letting review_id go through
seeded the database with not so random data and close to tennessee
Fixed Review creation and added YikYak integration
Driver uses get or create behavior on create
Added .ruby-version file to keep track of Ruby with rbenv
got the api back to stable. Still tryig to return the location_id instead of location when returning all drivers.

This is the restful api created for roadrant as it stands. Has all of the scaffolding for each of the elements as well as a seed file that can be used to populate the database for testing purposes. The api will return json with the proper serialization for the element(s) requested.
